				<div class="postbody">
				I think a lot of the misconceptions come from two primary sources--one, despite all the prostelizing, the church keeps pretty much to itself. Unlike the catholic church where the pope takes a press conference on every world happening, you don't see the LDS church stepping much into the world political stage. They seem to mostly be about keeping their internal politics/members taken care of. 
<br />
Which leads to reason two--the church is is really good at isolating itself. Because of the time requirements and the social intricasies, most Mormon families associate primarly with other Morman families. So this limits the exposure of 'normal' church followers to the outside world and hence the rumors spread without a lot of rational folks to dispute them. Besides, we the people are always more willing to believe the freaky gossip over the more rational explanations. (if not believe, per se, we are definitely more likely to repeat it!)
<br />

<br />
My boyfriend of three years was raised Mormon--did the whole mission thing and everything. Yes, they have some funky beliefs--he told me about the Kolab thing, and I tease him about his magical underwear. I will have to ask him about the naked annointing.<br />
